  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Age &gt;18 years-old

          -  High axial myopia &lt; -6 dioptries

          -  Presence or not of lacquer cracks in Bruch's membrane in one or both eyes

          -  Patients with social security coverage

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age &lt;18 years-old

          -  Amblyopia in the studied eye

          -  Prior ocular surgery

          -  Corneal disease or severe dry eye syndrome

          -  Other retinal disease: diabetic retinopathy, age-related macular degeneration, macular
             hole, epiretinal membrane central

          -  Extensive chorioretinal atrophy

          -  Allergy to tropicamide

          -  Pregnancy
      </textblock>
